## Cursor Behaviour
- When asked to create a file, create the complete file. No placeholders.
- When asked to scaffold a module, create all files in the module (controller, service, module, dto).
- When writing Tailwind, always think mobile-first: base styles for mobile, md: for tablet, lg: for desktop.
- When writing animations, use Framer Motion variants with staggerChildren.
- Always add db indexes on foreign keys and frequently queried columns.
- When writing Python, always use async def and await for IO operations.
